      • How to Connect Smart Watch?

        1.Turn on the watch and your phones Bluetooth.

        2.Open the app, go to the "Device", click "Add Device," select G53, and connect.

        3.Ensure the app runs in the phones background without manual closure or power-saving to maintain the watch connection.

      • How to get SMS messages and other social notifications? NOTE: CAN NOT SEND MESSAGE!!!!

        In the App:

        Open all apps that require push notifications.

        On the Phone Setting:

        Allow all permissions for the app and any app that requires notifications, including pop-ups, reminders, and landscape mode.

        NOTE: ONLY RECEIVE,CAN NOT SEND MESSAGE!!!!

      • Why Step count is not accurate at allPushing a stroller it doesn't count any of your steps?

        The accuracy of data relie on accurate personal info in the app. Step data: Shake your wrist to activate the watch, then it tracks steps. Sleep data: Wear the watch correctly at night, ensuring the back is close to your wrist for accurate monitoring.

      • Can't get all contacts in the watch?

        1) If there are special characters or long numbers, change them to normal contact names and numbers.

        2) In the contact person, the phone number must be preceded by a 1 or +1, and there must be no brackets in the area code.

      • Why the watch faces or bands look different from the website? Tips: The size of the watch band is 20mm

        1.Open the app, go to "Settings," then select "Watch Face." From there, you can choose your favorite design.

        2. WE offer THREE WATCH BANDS: a silicone band, a breathable perforated band, and a woven nylon band. You can choose your favorite band!

        I was looking for a new smart/fitness watch that I would be able to purchase in my affordability range. I was searching for one that met all of my features requirements:

        1. Standard date & time easily displayed by default on the watch face.
        2. Programmable alarm.
        3. Step tracker.
        4. Sleep tracker.
        5. Blood pressure measurement.
        6. Pulse & Oxygen measurement.
        7. Stress level tracker.
        8. Long operation time between charging.
        9. Quick charge.
        10. Compatibility with multiple mobile devices. (In my case a Samsung S24 Android smartphone).
        11. Easy to learn/use device app.
        12. Nice watch face screen designs.
        13. Nice wristband that wears well, in which the extra length of the band can be kept out of the way, and doesn't come unhitched during use.
        14. Is not incredibly expensive.

        After a long search, I came across this beauty. It has ALL of my requirements, plus quite a few more features I never really thought of. For example, the watch is able to monitor TONS of different specific types of sports played (like basketball, football, and even DANCING). It is able to save each one separately.

        The watch comes with two different design styles of wristband: one nicely decorative, the other much more basic. I LOVE the fact that the more decorative has a hoop aside from the hitch that you can tuck your extra strap length through to keep it out of the way, as well as keep it from being damaged and unhitched during use.

        As a bonus, it has a very nice selection of watch screen faces. The app gets updated with new types of designs, as well. My design I liked best was the analog, traditional watch face with arms (the kind this new generation of kids usually don't know how read). I chose the design that echoes my favorite art/design era of Art Deco.

        If you are looking for a wonderful smart/fitness watch, one with very robust features for a price that doesn't break the bank, I highly recommend getting this one!

        It's easy to set up. It's cool that it will monitor your heart rate your and your sleep patterns letting you know if you go into deep sleep or light sleep. It also measures your stress. Also gives you advice on how to breathe LOL. I don't really enjoy the sports mode One you always have to remember to turn it on, but you also have to find the particular exercise you're doing in that moment and it has a wide range but not wide enough. I have found that the battery life is not as long as they say. I get 4 days before I have to charge it. I know it says waterproof but I've yet to take a shower with it because there's a difference between water resistant and actually waterproof.
        I think my biggest complaint is that because it's not a Fitbit or one of the mainstream ones. The app doesn't like to communicate with other apps. I am using MyFitness app to calculate my dietary calories. Unfortunately Google fit does not sync up well with it because it's not a Fitbit or one of the top 10 of that app. So I'm finding that my steps are not being calculated properly. On average, I do 17,000 steps a day 20% of the time. Those steps are calculated properly. The rest of the time it will show maybe 12 steps or completely zero. If you're willing to go just off your watch, this is a great fitness watch especially for its price point it will not break the bank and it does calculate a lot of your calories for you.
